called for greater transparency in derivatives trading a stance at odds with many other hedge funds and major financial firms the company spoke out against wall street for lobbying to delay the implementation of the doddfrank act griffin has also called for breaking up too big to fail banks and separating their banking and trading activities following the  publication of flash boys by michael lewis who claimed financial markets are rigged by highfrequency traders at the expense of smaller investors griffin became a highprofile defender of todays markets pushing for the transformation from a dealerdominated model to one that is more transparent automated and competitive griffin claimed us equity markets are the fairest most transparent resilient and competitive in the world before the senate banking committee as a part of a series called citadel conversations stephen berger spoke out advocating for fair open and transparent markets officesedit citadel employs more than  individuals globally with its flagship operation located in the citadel center a  million office tower in the heart of downtown chicago the story citadel center office tower opened in  with citadel as its anchor tenant citadel also has offices in new york hong kong san francisco boston dallas london houston greenwich denver shenzen shanghai and toronto philanthropyedit citadel is an active participant in the community by providing educational opportunities and helping children and families with acute medical needs the firm also partners with food banks around the united states for a virtual food drive in  citadels contributions to the greater chicago food depository were the highest from a single corporate donor in that organizations history citadel leads a business plan competition for the national foundation for teaching entrepreneurship mentoring low income high school students in january  citadel partnered with the national museum of mathematics momath to tutor prepare and support math and science